Creating Symbolic Links:

ln -s <filename> <newfile>: Create links between files.
Example: ln -s ramadan25 roza25, ln -s /opt/securityonion /home/secondonion.
Disk Usage:

df -h: Display disk space usage in a human-readable format.
Listing Files and Inodes:

ls -i <directory>: List files with inode numbers.
ls -il <directory>: List files with detailed information.
Creating Empty Files:

touch <filename>: Create empty files.
Example: touch .rat, touch .filename.
User Management:

useradd <username>: Add new users.
Example: useradd fighter5, ln -s /usr/sbin/useradd /usr/sbin/userbnao.
Copying Files and Directories:

cp <source> <destination>: Copy files and directories.
Example: cp /var/test /usr/ (file), cp -r /var/oracle /usr/ (directory).
Moving/Renaming Files and Directories:

mv <filename> <newfilename>: Move or rename files and directories.
Example: mv /var/dynamodb/ /mnt/.
